<dl id="n05048d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05048d">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05048d"> 48(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> When adam delved / And Eve span / Who was then the gentleman? / The serpent </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n25067a" href="n25all.htm#n25067a">N25 (VI.B.15):067(a)</a>. When English peasants and artsians rebelled against feudalism in 1381, their slogan was the couplet preached by John Ball at Blackheath: &ldquo;When Adam delved, and Eve span, who was then the gentleman?&rdquo; </mm> </dd></dl>
